Hm2DeviceExtNVMType.name: Hm2DeviceExtNVMType
Hm2DeviceExtNVMType.description: Type of an external non volatile memory device.

hm2DevMgmtProductId.name: hm2DevMgmtProductId
hm2DevMgmtProductId.description: Manufacturer-defined product identifier (product family + product ID). Example:Objekt-ID 1.3.6.1.4.1.248.11.2.1.1 is the hm2ProductFamily EES and Objekt-ID 1.3.6.1.4.1.248.11.2.1.1.2 is the Product ID for ees25-0600

hm2DevMgmtSerialNumber.name: hm2DevMgmtSerialNumber
hm2DevMgmtSerialNumber.description: Manufacturer-defined serial number of the device.

hm2DevMgmtActionReset.name: hm2DevMgmtActionReset
hm2DevMgmtActionReset.description: Setting the object to 'reset' has the same effect as a power-on sequence (cold start) Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushFDB.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushFDB
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushFDB.description: Setting the object to 'flushFDB' will flush the forwarding database of the switch. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushARP.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushARP
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushARP.description: Setting the object to 'flushARP' will flush the ARP cache. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushIGS.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushIGS
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushIGS.description: Setting the object to 'flushIGS' will flush all dynamically learnt IGMP snooping entries. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushPortStats.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushPortStats
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushPortStats.description: Setting the object to 'flushPortStats' will flush all port statistics. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushEmailLogStats.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushEmailLogStats
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushEmailLogStats.description: Setting the object to 'flushEmailLogCounters' will flush all email logging statistics. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushMMRP.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushMMRP
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushMMRP.description: Setting the object to 'flushMMRP' will flush all MMRP counters. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushMVRP.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushMVRP
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushMVRP.description: Setting the object to 'flushMVRP' will flush all MVRP counters. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushMSRP.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushMSRP
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushMSRP.description: Setting the object to 'flushMSRP' will flush all MSRP counters. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushIeee8021AS.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushIeee8021AS
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushIeee8021AS.description: Setting the object to 'flushIeee8021AS' will flush all IEEE8021AS related counters. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushDnsClientCache.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushDnsClientCache
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushDnsClientCache.description: Setting the object to 'flushDnsClientCache' will flush all DNS client cache records. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushDnsCachingServerCac.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushDnsCachingServerCache
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushDnsCachingServerCac.description: Setting the object to 'flushDnsCachingServerCache' will flush all DNS caching server cache records. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushIpUdpHelperStats.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushIpUdpHelperStats
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushIpUdpHelperStats.description: Setting the object to 'flushIpUdpHelperStats' will flush all ip udp helper statistics. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushAclStats.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushAclStats
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushAclStats.description: Setting the object to 'flushAclStats' will flush all acl statistics from the AgentAclRuleTable. Setting the object to 'flushAclMacStats' will flush all acl statistics from the AgentAclMacRuleTable. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionFlushLdapUserCache.name: hm2DevMgmtActionFlushLdapUserCache
hm2DevMgmtActionFlushLdapUserCache.description: Setting the object to 'flushLdapUserCache' will flush all cached users from LDAP queries to an Active Directory Server. Reading the object always returns 'other'.

hm2DevMgmtActionDelayPreset.name: hm2DevMgmtActionDelayPreset
hm2DevMgmtActionDelayPreset.description: Time in seconds until a reset that was triggered over the hm2DevMgmtActionReset object is executed. Writing a zero will cancel any scheduled reset.

hm2DevMgmtActionDelayCurrent.name: hm2DevMgmtActionDelayCurrent
hm2DevMgmtActionDelayCurrent.description: If a delayed reset is scheduled this object will decrement from the start value to zero.

hm2DevMgmtSwVersBootcode.name: hm2DevMgmtSwVersBootcode
hm2DevMgmtSwVersBootcode.description: Software version of the boot code.

hm2DevMgmtSwVersTable.name: hm2DevMgmtSwVersTable
hm2DevMgmtSwVersTable.description: This table contains all information related to running and stored software versions on the device. The limit are 24 firmware (*.bin) files in up to 5 directory levels.

hm2DevMgmtSwFileLocation.name: hm2DevMgmtSwFileLocation
hm2DevMgmtSwFileLocation.description: Indicates the file location (ram, flash, sd-card or usb).

hm2DevMgmtSwFileType.name: hm2DevMgmtSwFileType
hm2DevMgmtSwFileType.description: Indicates the file type (firmware, applet, logic).

hm2DevMgmtSwFileIdx.name: hm2DevMgmtSwFileIdx
hm2DevMgmtSwFileIdx.description: Indicates the index. For flash the index has the following meaning: - flash.xxx.1 = bootable version in flash (ROM) - flash.xxx.2 = backup version in flash (BAK)

hm2DevMgmtSwMajorRelNum.name: hm2DevMgmtSwMajorRelNum
hm2DevMgmtSwMajorRelNum.description: Shows the major release number of the firmware.

hm2DevMgmtSwMinorRelNum.name: hm2DevMgmtSwMinorRelNum
hm2DevMgmtSwMinorRelNum.description: Shows the minor release number of the firmware.

hm2DevMgmtSwBugfixRelNum.name: hm2DevMgmtSwBugfixRelNum
hm2DevMgmtSwBugfixRelNum.description: Shows the bug fix release number of the firmware.

hm2DevMgmtLogicVersTable.name: hm2DevMgmtLogicVersTable
hm2DevMgmtLogicVersTable.description: The table displays all versions of supported logic modules.

hm2DevMgmtLogicIdx.name: hm2DevMgmtLogicIdx
hm2DevMgmtLogicIdx.description: Index of the module to display.

hm2DevMgmtLogicAddress.name: hm2DevMgmtLogicAddress
hm2DevMgmtLogicAddress.description: Address of the logic module in fpga.

hm2DevMgmtLogicVersion.name: hm2DevMgmtLogicVersion
hm2DevMgmtLogicVersion.description: Version of the logic module in fpga.

hm2DevMgmtTemperature.name: hm2DevMgmtTemperature
hm2DevMgmtTemperature.description: This object is used to identify the temperature within a device in units of centigrade (Celsius).

hm2DevMgmtTemperatureUpperLimit.name: hm2DevMgmtTemperatureUpperLimit
hm2DevMgmtTemperatureUpperLimit.description: This object is used to define a maximum level for the temperature within a device. If the temperature rises above this upper limit, the management station will be notified by a hm2DevMgmtTemperature trap.

hm2DevMgmtTemperatureLowerLimit.name: hm2DevMgmtTemperatureLowerLimit
hm2DevMgmtTemperatureLowerLimit.description: This object is used to define a minimum level for the temperature within a device. If the temperature falls below this lower limit, the management station will be notified by a hm2DevMgmtTemperature trap.

hm2IfaceTable.name: hm2IfaceTable
hm2IfaceTable.description: This table contains extended PHY capabilities and configuration options.

hm2IfaceEntry.name: hm2IfaceEntry
hm2IfaceEntry.description: Entry with the configuration options and supported features of a port.

hm2IfacePhysIndex.name: hm2IfacePhysIndex
hm2IfacePhysIndex.description: The index of the available physical interfaces.

hm2IfacePortCapabilityBits.name: hm2IfacePortCapabilityBits
hm2IfacePortCapabilityBits.description: manual-mdix - port supports MDIX and MDI auto-mdix - port supports MDIX and Auto-MDIX auto-power-down - port can enter low power mode if no link is established energy-efficient-ethernet - port supports EEE cable-test - port supports cable testing

hm2IfaceCableCrossing.name: hm2IfaceCableCrossing
hm2IfaceCableCrossing.description: This variable configures the cable crossing on twisted pair cables. When set to 'mdi', the device does not swap the send and receive line pairs of the TP cable for this port. When set to 'mdix', the device swaps the send and receive line pairs of the TP cable for this port. When set to 'auto-mdix', the port uses the auto crossover mode. 'Unsupported' is shown, if a port does not support cable crossing or auto-negotiation is disabled. It is not possible to set 'unsupported' to any type of port.

hm2IfacePowerState.name: hm2IfacePowerState
hm2IfacePowerState.description: This variable configures the power on the interface. When set to 'enable' that means the interface-power is on (power up) When set to 'disable' that means the interface-power is off (power down) The interface power state settings have no effect if the interface admin state (ifAdminStatus) is enabled

hm2IfaceAutoPowerDown.name: hm2IfaceAutoPowerDown
hm2IfaceAutoPowerDown.description: This variable configures the automatic power save mode on the interface. When set to 'auto-power-down', the port goes in a low power mode if no link is detected. When set to 'no-power-save', the port does not use the automatic power save mode. When set to 'energy-efficient-ethernet', the port uses energy-efficient-ethernet mode to save the power. 'Unsupported' is shown, if a port does not support automatic power save mode.

hm2IfaceOperAdminStatus.name: hm2IfaceOperAdminStatus
hm2IfaceOperAdminStatus.description: This variable shows the operational admin state of a specific interface. The operational state could be different to the ifAdminStatus if the interface is forced to down by other means like hm2AutoDisableIntfOperState.

hm2IfaceLayoutTable.name: hm2IfaceLayoutTable
hm2IfaceLayoutTable.description: This table does contain the layout of the interface modules or blocks. It contains all possible physical and logical items. This table can be used to determine any interface index according to 'IfEntry' that may exist and the name of this interface.

hm2IfaceLayoutEntry.name: hm2IfaceLayoutEntry
hm2IfaceLayoutEntry.description: An entry of a module or block of interfaces.

hm2IfaceLayoutIndex.name: hm2IfaceLayoutIndex
hm2IfaceLayoutIndex.description: The index used for this table.

hm2IfaceLayoutStartIfIndex.name: hm2IfaceLayoutStartIfIndex
hm2IfaceLayoutStartIfIndex.description: It specifies the first interface index of this block or module.

hm2IfaceLayoutEndIfIndex.name: hm2IfaceLayoutEndIfIndex
hm2IfaceLayoutEndIfIndex.description: It specifies the last interface index of this block or module that can exist for this particular device. The amount of interfaces between first and last may not be equal than to the maximum interface per module.

hm2IfaceLayoutModuleCapacity.name: hm2IfaceLayoutModuleCapacity
hm2IfaceLayoutModuleCapacity.description: It is the Number of modules in that block. Currently not used and it is always 0.

hm2IfaceLayoutModulePortCapacity.name: hm2IfaceLayoutModulePortCapacity
hm2IfaceLayoutModulePortCapacity.description: Number of interfaces that one module can contain. Currently not used and it is always 0

hm2IfaceLayoutFormat.name: hm2IfaceLayoutFormat
hm2IfaceLayoutFormat.description: This specifies a format string that can be used to determine the textual representation of an interface in this block. following wildcards are supported: %i the absolute interface number according to 'IfEntry'. %p the relative number based on hm2IfaceLayoutStartIfIndex %s the block number from 'hm2IfaceLayoutIndex' %vid the vlan of the routing interface %lre the name of the redundancy port (prp or hsr)

hm2IfaceLayoutIfIndexType.name: hm2IfaceLayoutIfIndexType
hm2IfaceLayoutIfIndexType.description: Type of the interfaces in that block according to IANA-Type table.

hm2IfaceExtTable.name: hm2IfaceExtTable
hm2IfaceExtTable.description: This table contains additional information about the interfaces.

hm2IfaceExtIfRole.name: hm2IfaceExtIfRole
hm2IfaceExtIfRole.description: The current role of the interface.

hm2SfpInfoTable.name: hm2SfpInfoTable
hm2SfpInfoTable.description: This table contains variables for each SFP.

hm2SfpModuleType.name: hm2SfpModuleType
hm2SfpModuleType.description: Type of the module. SFP or SFP+ (3), XFP (6).

hm2SfpVendorOUI.name: hm2SfpVendorOUI
hm2SfpVendorOUI.description: The vendor organizationally unique identifier field (OUI).

hm2SfpPartNumber.name: hm2SfpPartNumber
hm2SfpPartNumber.description: The part number of the module (ASCII).

hm2SfpPartRev.name: hm2SfpPartRev
hm2SfpPartRev.description: The revision number of the module (ASCII).

hm2SfpSerialNum.name: hm2SfpSerialNum
hm2SfpSerialNum.description: The SFP's serial number provided by vendor (ASCII).

hm2SfpDateCode.name: hm2SfpDateCode
hm2SfpDateCode.description: The SFP's vendor manufacturing date code. Format is YY:MM:DD.

hm2SfpInfoVersion.name: hm2SfpInfoVersion
hm2SfpInfoVersion.description: Version of SFP's Hirschmann information. Contains -1 in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpInfoPartNumber.name: hm2SfpInfoPartNumber
hm2SfpInfoPartNumber.description: Part Number of SFP's Hirschmann information.

hm2SfpInfoPartId.name: hm2SfpInfoPartId
hm2SfpInfoPartId.description: Part Identifier of SFP's Hirschmann information.

hm2SfpBitRateNominal.name: hm2SfpBitRateNominal
hm2SfpBitRateNominal.description: The SFP's nominal bitrate in units of MBits/sec. Contains -1 in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpBitRateMin.name: hm2SfpBitRateMin
hm2SfpBitRateMin.description: The minimum bit rate is specified in units of 100 Megabits per second, rounded off to the nearest 100 Megabits per second. A value of 0 indicates that the minimum bit rate is not specified.

hm2SfpBitRateMax.name: hm2SfpBitRateMax
hm2SfpBitRateMax.description: The maximum bit rate is specified in units of 100 Megabits per second, rounded off to the nearest 100 Megabits per second. A value of 0 indicates that the maximum bit rate is not specified.

hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_9.name: hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_9
hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_9.description: Max. usable length for the cable type '9/125 micrometer fiber' with this SFP in units of meters.

hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_50.name: hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_50
hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_50.description: Max. usable length for the cable type '50/125 micrometer fiber' with this SFP in units of meters.

hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_e50.name: hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_e50
hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_e50.description: Max. usable length for the cable type 'EBW 50/125 micrometer fiber' with this SFP in units of meters or -1 if not supported.

hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_62_5.name: hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_62_5
hm2SfpMaxLength_fiber_62_5.description: Max. usable length for the cable type '62.5/125 micrometer fiber' with this SFP in units of meters.

hm2SfpMaxLength_copper.name: hm2SfpMaxLength_copper
hm2SfpMaxLength_copper.description: Max. usable length for the cable type 'copper' with this SFP in units of meters.

hm2SfpWaveLength.name: hm2SfpWaveLength
hm2SfpWaveLength.description: Nominal transmitter output wavelength at room temperature. The laser wavelength in nm (units of 0.05nm).

hm2SfpWaveLengthTolerance.name: hm2SfpWaveLengthTolerance
hm2SfpWaveLengthTolerance.description: The +/- range of transmitter output wavelength under normal operating conditions or -1 if not supported.

hm2SfpSupported.name: hm2SfpSupported
hm2SfpSupported.description: The SFP is supported by the device (true) or not (false).

hm2SfpSupportedReason.name: hm2SfpSupportedReason
hm2SfpSupportedReason.description: The reason why this SFP is supported.

hm2SfpDiagTable.name: hm2SfpDiagTable
hm2SfpDiagTable.description: This table contains variables for each SFP.

hm2SfpCurrentBitRate.name: hm2SfpCurrentBitRate
hm2SfpCurrentBitRate.description: The current bit rate in units of Megabits per second.

hm2SfpCurrentTemperature.name: hm2SfpCurrentTemperature
hm2SfpCurrentTemperature.description: This signed integer is used to identify the temperature within the SFP in units of centigrade (Celsius). Contains -1000 in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpCurrentTxPower.name: hm2SfpCurrentTxPower
hm2SfpCurrentTxPower.description: The SFP's internally measured Tx Power in units of 1/10 microwatt or -1 if it is not supported.

hm2SfpCurrentRxPower.name: hm2SfpCurrentRxPower
hm2SfpCurrentRxPower.description: The SFP's internally measured Rx Power in units of 1/10 microWatts or -10000 if not supportted.

hm2SfpCurrentTxPowerdBm.name: hm2SfpCurrentTxPowerdBm
hm2SfpCurrentTxPowerdBm.description: The SFP's internally measured Tx Power in units of dBm. (ASCII representation of a floating point number). - if not supported.

hm2SfpCurrentRxPowerdBm.name: hm2SfpCurrentRxPowerdBm
hm2SfpCurrentRxPowerdBm.description: The SFP's internally measured Rx Power in units of dBm. (ASCII representation of a floating point number). - if not supported.

hm2SfpCurrentRxPowerState.name: hm2SfpCurrentRxPowerState
hm2SfpCurrentRxPowerState.description: The state of the SFP's internally measured Rx.

hm2SfpWLStatus.name: hm2SfpWLStatus
hm2SfpWLStatus.description: Status of the SFP White List. present(1): a white list is present on the device absent(2): no white list is present on the device not-supported(3): white list feature is not supported in this device

hm2SfpThresholdTable.name: hm2SfpThresholdTable
hm2SfpThresholdTable.description: This table contains the thresholds for each SFP.

hm2SfpTemperatureHighAlarm.name: hm2SfpTemperatureHighAlarm
hm2SfpTemperatureHighAlarm.description: The SFP's Temperature High Alarm threshold in units of centigrade (Celsius). It is -1000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTemperatureHighWarning.name: hm2SfpTemperatureHighWarning
hm2SfpTemperatureHighWarning.description: The SFP's Temperature High Warning threshold in units of centigrade (Celsius). It is -1000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTemperatureLowAlarm.name: hm2SfpTemperatureLowAlarm
hm2SfpTemperatureLowAlarm.description: The SFP's Temperature Low Alarm threshold in units of centigrade (Celsius). It is -1000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTemperatureLowWarning.name: hm2SfpTemperatureLowWarning
hm2SfpTemperatureLowWarning.description: The SFP's Temperature Low Warning threshold in units of centigrade (Celsius). It is -1000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTxPowerHighAlarm.name: hm2SfpTxPowerHighAlarm
hm2SfpTxPowerHighAlarm.description: The SFP's Tx Power High Alarm threshold in units of 0.1uW. It is -10000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTxPowerHighWarning.name: hm2SfpTxPowerHighWarning
hm2SfpTxPowerHighWarning.description: The SFP's Tx Power High Warning threshold in units of 0.1uW. It is -10000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTxPowerLowAlarm.name: hm2SfpTxPowerLowAlarm
hm2SfpTxPowerLowAlarm.description: The SFP's Tx Power Low Alarm threshold in units of 0.1uW. It is -10000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTxPowerLowWarning.name: hm2SfpTxPowerLowWarning
hm2SfpTxPowerLowWarning.description: The SFP's Tx Power Low Warning threshold in units of 0.1uW. It is -10000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpRxPowerHighAlarm.name: hm2SfpRxPowerHighAlarm
hm2SfpRxPowerHighAlarm.description: The SFP's Rx Power High Alarm threshold in units of 0.1uW. It is -10000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpRxPowerHighWarning.name: hm2SfpRxPowerHighWarning
hm2SfpRxPowerHighWarning.description: The SFP's Rx Power High Warning threshold in units of 0.1uW. It is -10000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpRxPowerLowAlarm.name: hm2SfpRxPowerLowAlarm
hm2SfpRxPowerLowAlarm.description: The SFP's Rx Power Low Alarm threshold in units of 0.1uW. It is -10000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpRxPowerLowWarning.name: hm2SfpRxPowerLowWarning
hm2SfpRxPowerLowWarning.description: The SFP's Rx Power Low Warning threshold in units of 0.1uW. It is -10000 if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTxPowerdBmHighAlarm.name: hm2SfpTxPowerdBmHighAlarm
hm2SfpTxPowerdBmHighAlarm.description: The SFP's Tx Power High Alarm threshold in units of dBm (ASCII representation of floating point number). It is N/A if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTxPowerdBmHighWarning.name: hm2SfpTxPowerdBmHighWarning
hm2SfpTxPowerdBmHighWarning.description: The SFP's Tx Power High Warning threshold in units of dBm (ASCII representation of floating point number). It is N/A if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTxPowerdBmLowAlarm.name: hm2SfpTxPowerdBmLowAlarm
hm2SfpTxPowerdBmLowAlarm.description: The SFP's Tx Power Low Alarm threshold in units of dBm (ASCII representation of floating point number). It is N/A if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpTxPowerdBmLowWarning.name: hm2SfpTxPowerdBmLowWarning
hm2SfpTxPowerdBmLowWarning.description: The SFP's Tx Power Low Warning threshold in units of dBm (ASCII representation of floating point number). It is N/A if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpRxPowerdBmHighAlarm.name: hm2SfpRxPowerdBmHighAlarm
hm2SfpRxPowerdBmHighAlarm.description: The SFP's Rx Power High Alarm threshold in units of dBm (ASCII representation of floating point number). It is N/A if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpRxPowerdBmHighWarning.name: hm2SfpRxPowerdBmHighWarning
hm2SfpRxPowerdBmHighWarning.description: The SFP's Rx Power High Warning threshold in units of dBm (ASCII representation of floating point number). It is N/A if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpRxPowerdBmLowAlarm.name: hm2SfpRxPowerdBmLowAlarm
hm2SfpRxPowerdBmLowAlarm.description: The SFP's Rx Power Low Alarm threshold in units of dBm (ASCII representation of floating point number). It is N/A if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2SfpRxPowerdBmLowWarning.name: hm2SfpRxPowerdBmLowWarning
hm2SfpRxPowerdBmLowWarning.description: The SFP's Rx Power Low Warning threshold in units of dBm (ASCII representation of floating point number). It is N/A if the SFP device does not support it or in case of a device read error.

hm2ExtNvmChooseActive.name: hm2ExtNvmChooseActive
hm2ExtNvmChooseActive.description: The user can choose which external NV memory to use for file operations.

hm2ExtNvmLogDevice.name: hm2ExtNvmLogDevice
hm2ExtNvmLogDevice.description: The user can choose which external NV memory to use for persistent logging.

hm2ExtNvmAdminMode.name: hm2ExtNvmAdminMode
hm2ExtNvmAdminMode.description: Switches the USB bus between High Speed (normal) and Full Speed (compatibility). This setting only takes effect after a reboot.

hm2ExtNvmOperMode.name: hm2ExtNvmOperMode
hm2ExtNvmOperMode.description: Shows the USB mode the device is currently operating in.

hm2ExtNvmTable.name: hm2ExtNvmTable
hm2ExtNvmTable.description: This table contains variables for each nvram.

hm2ExtNvmStatus.name: hm2ExtNvmStatus
hm2ExtNvmStatus.description: Status of the external non-volatile memory. notPresent(1): external non-volatile memory has not been detected. removed(2): external non-volatile memory was removed in running mode of the agent. ok(3): external non-volatile memory is present and OK. outOfMemory(4): external non-volatile memory is full. genericErr(5): Any other failure, e.g. hardware malfunction.

hm2ExtNvmSerialNum.name: hm2ExtNvmSerialNum
hm2ExtNvmSerialNum.description: The serial number provided by vendor (ASCII).

hm2ExtNvmAutomaticSoftwareLoad.name: hm2ExtNvmAutomaticSoftwareLoad
hm2ExtNvmAutomaticSoftwareLoad.description: Enable or disable Automatic loading of a software image from the external non-volatile memory. A file named 'startup.txt' must be present on the external non-volatile memory and contain the line 'autoUpdate=filename'.

hm2ExtNvmConfigLoadPriority.name: hm2ExtNvmConfigLoadPriority
hm2ExtNvmConfigLoadPriority.description: Set the priority of this external non-volatile memory for loading the configuration while booting. The configuration on the device with the lowest priority is loaded. Setting this variable to 0 disables loading of a configuration from this device.

hm2ExtNvmConfigSave.name: hm2ExtNvmConfigSave
hm2ExtNvmConfigSave.description: Enable or disable Automatic saving of the configuration to the external non-volatile memory. If this is enabled, saving the configuration of the device to its internal nvram also stores in on this external nvram.

hm2ExtNvmWritable.name: hm2ExtNvmWritable
hm2ExtNvmWritable.description: Shows if writing to the device is possible, i.e. if it is write protected.

hm2ExtNvmAutomaticSshKeyLoad.name: hm2ExtNvmAutomaticSshKeyLoad
hm2ExtNvmAutomaticSshKeyLoad.description: Enable or disable automatic loading of a SSH key from the external non-volatile memory. A file named 'startup.txt' must be present on the external non-volatile memory and contain the line 'autoUpdateRSA=' and/or 'autoUpdateDSA='.

hm2AutoDisableIntfRemainingTime.name: hm2AutoDisableIntfRemainingTime
hm2AutoDisableIntfRemainingTime.description: Remaining time in seconds until the re-activation of the port.

hm2AutoDisableIntfComponentName.name: hm2AutoDisableIntfComponentName
hm2AutoDisableIntfComponentName.description: Name of the component that triggered the error

hm2AutoDisableIntfTimer.name: hm2AutoDisableIntfTimer
hm2AutoDisableIntfTimer.description: Timer value in seconds after a deactivated port is activated again. Possible values are: 30-4294967295. A value of 0 disables the timer.

hm2AutoDisableIntfOperState.name: hm2AutoDisableIntfOperState
hm2AutoDisableIntfOperState.description: Status of Auto Disable interface admin state. Active means that a component has encountered an error and Auto-Disable has turned off the interface. Inactive means that currently there is no error

hm2AutoDisableIntfErrorTime.name: hm2AutoDisableIntfErrorTime
hm2AutoDisableIntfErrorTime.description: Local system time (hm2SystemLocalTime) when the error occured.

hm2AutoDisableReasonOperation.name: hm2AutoDisableReasonOperation
